1
00:00:01,530 --> 00:00:05,490
Episode 6

2
00:00:25,420 --> 00:00:27,320
Hong Yi Yeong!

3
00:00:38,450 --> 00:00:40,470
Hong Yi Yeong.

4
00:00:49,760 --> 00:00:54,670
♫ The wind gives and leaves...

5
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:58,810
It's a shame but I'll return it to you.

6
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:09,420
The wind does what?

7
00:01:14,230 --> 00:01:16,530
Your bra?

8
00:01:18,270 --> 00:01:21,630
Be quiet please.

9
00:01:21,630 --> 00:01:28,430
So, Jang Yun gave you your bra?

10
00:01:28,430 --> 00:01:30,270
Yes, I told you so.

11
00:01:30,270 --> 00:01:33,080
That man is strange.

12
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:36,620
Explaining would be too long, but there are too many strange events around him.

13
00:01:37,790 --> 00:01:41,000
Your bra probably flew out with the wind, you leave your laundry everywhere.

14
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,230
I said that's not it.

15
00:01:42,230 --> 00:01:44,820
What do you mean it's not?

16
00:01:44,820 --> 00:01:48,920
Why would he steal your bra? If he stole it, you would have known.

17
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:51,600
I'm being very serious right now.

18
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:54,970
All right, let's say you're serious...

19
00:01:54,970 --> 00:01:57,120
Did you hear it?  The rumor about Maestro Nam?

20
00:01:57,120 --> 00:02:00,960
Maestro Nam?  No.  What rumor?

21
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:05,410
I think it worked out for Eun Ju.

22
00:02:07,990 --> 00:02:08,730
No way!

23
00:02:08,730 --> 00:02:10,500
No, really!

24
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:12,900
Eun Ju is not your average girl.

25
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:17,460
For the inaugural concert this time, we will be playing some concertos. Some orchestra members weren't even invited.

26
00:02:17,460 --> 00:02:22,150
But the ending piece, it's not Jo Hak Jang doing it but Ha Eun Ju.

27
00:02:22,150 --> 00:02:22,930
Seriously?

28
00:02:22,930 --> 00:02:24,940
I'm serious.

29
00:02:24,940 --> 00:02:29,510
Even if you believe Maestro Nam, in the end he is a man.

30
00:02:29,510 --> 00:02:31,990
I have to go to my lesson.

31
00:02:31,990 --> 00:02:36,350
Don't be too sad. When I get my paycheck, I'll buy.

32
00:02:36,350 --> 00:02:39,590
I'm going.

33
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:56,590
I said no, why do you keep insisting?

34
00:02:56,590 --> 00:02:59,860
The conductor is resting right now.

35
00:02:59,860 --> 00:03:01,950
Please save me, huh?

36
00:03:01,950 --> 00:03:04,790
If he wakes up when he's resting, I'm dead.

37
00:03:04,790 --> 00:03:08,380
You know the conductor's personality, I'm actually going to get fired.

38
00:03:08,380 --> 00:03:09,730
It'll just be one minute.

39
00:03:09,730 --> 00:03:11,320
Just one minute. Can't I just meet him for one minute?

40
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:13,850
How many times do I have to tell you?

41
00:03:13,850 --> 00:03:16,720
An outsider can't just meet him without a reservation.

42
00:03:20,670 --> 00:03:22,960
An outsider?

43
00:03:25,370 --> 00:03:28,050
The payment  is 48,350 won.

44
00:03:28,050 --> 00:03:29,670
What?

45
00:03:31,010 --> 00:03:34,790
What I earned for working a day and a half.

46
00:03:34,790 --> 00:03:37,650
48,350 won.

47
00:03:37,650 --> 00:03:39,460
It doesn't seem like much right?

48
00:03:39,460 --> 00:03:41,630
But it is a very precious amount to me.

49
00:03:41,630 --> 00:03:45,810
Do you know why I haven't spent it and it's still in my bank account?

50
00:03:47,390 --> 00:03:49,960
Because I received the money from working here.

51
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:53,790
I got this from the place that I've been dreaming of for 15 years.

52
00:03:54,580 --> 00:03:56,790
Assistant Manager.

53
00:03:56,790 --> 00:04:00,870
You don't know much I've been playing the timpani, do you?

54
00:04:02,270 --> 00:04:05,260
Do you see these?  These  biceps?

55
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:08,380
Do you think these here are from exercise?

56
00:04:08,380 --> 00:04:12,000
Because I kept banging the mallets,

57
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:14,280
I got these bulging biceps on my arms.

58
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:16,130
Did you ever build biceps from practice?

59
00:04:16,130 --> 00:04:18,990
While I was practicing. Look.

60
00:04:18,990 --> 00:04:22,140
My precious biceps...

61
00:04:22,140 --> 00:04:25,010
My biceps have all burst.

62
00:04:26,060 --> 00:04:28,990
Why without knowing the first degree, won't you let me see  him?

63
00:04:28,990 --> 00:04:31,850
Is that all there is for the Sinyeong Philharmonic? If he's a genius, do you put him up on a pedestal?

64
00:04:31,850 --> 00:04:33,640
Why do geniuses shine brightly?

65
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:35,440
It's because of people like me.

66
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:38,990
Coming to work dressed as Mozart, the super attention getting subject.

67
00:04:48,620 --> 00:04:51,410
Have your biceps really burst?

68
00:04:54,130 --> 00:04:55,860
Let me see.

69
00:05:09,410 --> 00:05:11,400
Coffee?

70
00:05:16,270 --> 00:05:20,570
Look here, Conductor. I'm sorry about what I said out there.

71
00:05:20,570 --> 00:05:24,480
I never really meant super attention getter.

72
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:29,150
No, no, no.  There's nothing to apologize for. Attention-getter matches me. Whatever.

73
00:05:29,150 --> 00:05:34,160
So, what do you have to say for a minute?

74
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:40,700
Work...

75
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:42,420
Work?

76
00:05:47,330 --> 00:05:51,210
Give me anything to do, as long as I can stay.

77
00:05:51,210 --> 00:05:55,160
I want to learn more here and practice, so I can stand on stage again.

78
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:57,140
I'll work hard, so please let me stay.

79
00:05:57,140 --> 00:06:00,270
I'll do whatever you want, so please.

80
00:06:01,840 --> 00:06:03,690
Okay.

81
00:06:05,450 --> 00:06:06,100
What?

82
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:08,290
Anyway you are just what I need.

83
00:06:08,290 --> 00:06:09,980
Me?

84
00:06:09,980 --> 00:06:13,950
You see, I needed an assistant.

85
00:06:13,950 --> 00:06:18,720
You won't get to perform nor get much money but you can learn something by sticking with me.

86
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:20,770
You can also get opportunities more easily.

87
00:06:20,770 --> 00:06:24,560
You get me coffee before every rehearsal and manage my schedule for me.

88
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:28,580
You will even answer my phone.  You will add my notes to my sheet music.

89
00:06:28,580 --> 00:06:30,110
Okay?

90
00:06:32,210 --> 00:06:34,190
Okay.

91
00:06:34,190 --> 00:06:36,030
Okay.

92
00:06:37,370 --> 00:06:39,100
Okay.

93
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:02,760
Ms. Ha Eun Ju, you can come over here.

94
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:11,380
Crazy bitch.

95
00:08:11,380 --> 00:08:15,560
Why? Are you scared that I actually reported you?

96
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:20,020
Shut up, before I break all the other fingers.

97
00:08:20,020 --> 00:08:23,440
You heard that right? I'm a flutist.

98
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:25,140
Isn't that a murder threat? Hey!

99
00:08:25,140 --> 00:08:27,420
Get on your knees and apologize right now.

100
00:08:27,420 --> 00:08:29,260
You should make an acceptable apology.

101
00:08:29,260 --> 00:08:33,650
If you don't settle, you will be prosecuted.  Even it is just a fine, it's a criminal conviction.

102
00:08:33,650 --> 00:08:35,040
She has a criminal record anyway.

103
00:08:35,040 --> 00:08:38,070
She has two assault convictions.

104
00:08:38,070 --> 00:08:42,900
You think that's it? She also sells her body.

105
00:08:42,900 --> 00:08:45,420
How you got your hands on the Guadagnini? (Third best antique violin)

106
00:08:45,420 --> 00:08:48,430
should I tell him everything here and now?

107
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:11,760
I got this Quadagnini from my dad.

108
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:12,610
What?

109
00:09:12,610 --> 00:09:16,010
What can I do about your pitiful mom?

110
00:09:18,130 --> 00:09:21,230
You can sue me.

111
00:09:21,230 --> 00:09:23,830
You crazy wrench!

112
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:26,290
Really, how much...

113
00:09:26,290 --> 00:09:28,000
Get her!

114
00:09:40,830 --> 00:09:43,040
Conductor?

115
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:45,060
Oh, I'm sorry.

116
00:09:47,980 --> 00:09:50,320
Conductor's Room

117
00:09:52,590 --> 00:09:54,390
Who are you?

118
00:09:57,030 --> 00:09:58,800
Im Hong Yi Yeong, Office Manager.

119
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:01,950
Why are you here?

120
00:10:01,950 --> 00:10:04,080
I was hired by the conductor today.

121
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,830
Hired?

122
00:10:06,810 --> 00:10:10,870
Where is Nam Ju Wan? No matter how many times I call him, he doesn't answer.

123
00:10:10,870 --> 00:10:13,150
I'm not sure myself.

124
00:10:13,150 --> 00:10:15,250
He told me not to call him.

125
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:17,250
What did you say?

126
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:23,740
Hong Yi Yeong, listen to me carefully.

127
00:10:23,740 --> 00:10:26,930
I got a super expensive limousine and

128
00:10:26,930 --> 00:10:29,290
a restaurant reservation.

129
00:10:29,290 --> 00:10:32,540
- You got that?
- Y-Yes.

130
00:10:32,540 --> 00:10:35,710
Go out right now and find Maestro Nam.

131
00:10:35,710 --> 00:10:38,550
Give him the right clothes

132
00:10:40,940 --> 00:10:43,340
and bring him here.

133
00:10:54,090 --> 00:10:56,650
Conductor, I'm on my way there.

134
00:10:56,650 --> 00:10:59,000
Stay where you are.

135
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:11,290
Conductor?

136
00:11:14,420 --> 00:11:17,030
Conductor?

137
00:11:17,030 --> 00:11:19,400
Conductor?

138
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:26,860
Conductor.

139
00:11:29,110 --> 00:11:31,380
Conductor, I got the suit you told me to get.

140
00:11:31,380 --> 00:11:33,930
Please change and get ready to leave.

141
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:41,020
Lie down.

142
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:42,620
What?

143
00:11:46,010 --> 00:11:47,640
Sure.

144
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:00,060
How is it?

145
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:02,400
What?

146
00:12:03,860 --> 00:12:05,970
Do you hear it?

147
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,500
Hear what?

148
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:11,420
Beethoven.

149
00:12:11,420 --> 00:12:13,490
Beethoven?

150
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:23,040
Conductor, it's getting very late...

151
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:34,590
It's too late...

152
00:12:35,430 --> 00:12:37,740
What is this?

153
00:12:37,740 --> 00:12:40,130
What does he want with me?

154
00:12:42,980 --> 00:12:44,720
Hong Yi Yeong,

155
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:52,090
Yes?

156
00:12:52,090 --> 00:12:55,930
The day of the audition, I saw.

157
00:12:55,930 --> 00:12:57,470
Yes?

158
00:12:58,440 --> 00:13:01,900
What shined brightly within you.

159
00:13:05,630 --> 00:13:10,650
From now on, you must take that shiny thing out and polish it well.

160
00:13:10,650 --> 00:13:13,450
Don't let anyone step over you.

161
00:13:13,450 --> 00:13:17,020
So that no one bashes you.

162
00:13:21,460 --> 00:13:23,760
Remember,

163
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:26,900
one day we will stand on this stage together.

164
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:40,550
It's too bad.

165
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:41,790
What is?

166
00:13:41,790 --> 00:13:45,020
This is the perfect time for a kiss.

167
00:13:49,690 --> 00:13:54,890
Then, shall we go?

168
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:02,030
Sunbaenim, I mean conductor!

169
00:14:02,030 --> 00:14:03,920
You need to change first.

170
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:05,970
Conductor!

171
00:14:06,830 --> 00:14:11,790
That's what he said, that he needed an assistant.

172
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:16,490
He really is unpredictable.

173
00:14:16,490 --> 00:14:20,510
Anyway, good for you Hong Yi Yeong,  you did your best thinking to call on  Maestro Nam.

174
00:14:20,510 --> 00:14:23,060
Is just firing me every time the rule?

175
00:14:23,060 --> 00:14:25,610
I'm going to make effective use of my time from now on.

176
00:14:25,610 --> 00:14:31,670
Okay, okay. Tomorrow I'm going to blow up the chat line.

177
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:32,390
Are you?

178
00:14:32,390 --> 00:14:35,380
It's the carrot, dummy.  Would  Yu Da stand still reading that?

179
00:14:35,380 --> 00:14:37,370
Be careful for the time being.

180
00:14:37,370 --> 00:14:41,410
If not, this may be an opportunity for Maestro Nam to attack you.

181
00:14:41,410 --> 00:14:45,640
You are always telling me that.

182
00:14:45,640 --> 00:14:47,530
I'm hanging up.

183
00:14:48,390 --> 00:14:50,290
Thank you.

184
00:15:05,340 --> 00:15:07,760
Where did he go this late?

185
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:10,760
We didn't have a rehearsal today.

186
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:13,530
A lot of things are strange. What is strange about that?

187
00:16:13,530 --> 00:16:14,890
Jong Yun's partner.

188
00:16:14,890 --> 00:16:17,720
We met coincidentally more than three times. How is it not strange?

189
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:21,160
He gave me his number, then I saw him at the Sinyeong Philharmonic audition.

190
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:25,560
And now, out of this large neighborhood, he's moved right next to me.

191
00:16:26,700 --> 00:16:29,700
Do you really think I'm a stalker?

192
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:34,790
Tonight,

193
00:16:34,790 --> 00:16:38,580
I'm going to take off your mask, no matter what.

194
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:48,260
It's- it's a thief!

195
00:17:48,260 --> 00:17:50,090
It's a thief!

196
00:17:51,110 --> 00:17:53,330
A thief!

197
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:06,820
Call the police!

198
00:18:06,820 --> 00:18:08,820
What should I do?

199
00:18:08,820 --> 00:18:10,800
This is the police?

200
00:18:56,140 --> 00:18:58,070
Did you catch him?

201
00:19:05,470 --> 00:19:07,190
What?

202
00:19:09,290 --> 00:19:11,170
Why are you..?

203
00:19:28,290 --> 00:19:30,390
What are we going to do?

204
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:37,070
Noona, I wasn't going to do anything bad.

205
00:19:37,070 --> 00:19:39,160
Noona, please trust me.

206
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:41,000
Noona!

207
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:42,970
Noona!

208
00:19:49,990 --> 00:19:52,030
It's alright.

209
00:20:15,550 --> 00:20:18,740
Jae Hyeong broke into my home three times in all.

210
00:20:18,740 --> 00:20:22,500
Do you have some sort of relationship with Min Jae Hyeong?

211
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:26,320
The first time he broke into my home was because he was worried.

212
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:31,420
The second  time, when I didn't respond twice to his texts, in a fit of anger...

213
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:35,850
to use my home...

214
00:20:36,810 --> 00:20:42,170
The last time, he said he came in to give me a Brahms CD as a present.

215
00:20:51,010 --> 00:20:54,760
I wonder when will the moment come for love's passion to cool down.

216
00:20:56,200 --> 00:21:00,590
I wonder if love is truly a pure emotion.

217
00:21:19,050 --> 00:21:19,970
What is this?

218
00:21:19,970 --> 00:21:22,680
What do you think it is?

219
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:25,030
I'm saying open it for me.

220
00:21:41,170 --> 00:21:42,460
Are you busy?

221
00:21:42,460 --> 00:21:43,190
Why?

222
00:21:43,190 --> 00:21:46,090
You have to go somewhere with me.

223
00:21:46,090 --> 00:21:47,520
Right now?

224
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:48,550
I'm in pain.

225
00:21:48,550 --> 00:21:49,400
I can't even eat.

226
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:50,540
I can't even wash up.

227
00:21:50,540 --> 00:21:51,360
I can't drive either.

228
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:53,650
A pianist can't play piano.

229
00:21:53,650 --> 00:21:57,560
This is no different than dying.

230
00:22:20,610 --> 00:22:22,570
Wake me up when we arrive.

231
00:22:22,570 --> 00:22:25,410
Drive carefully.

232
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:30,610
Gangwon-do...

233
00:22:30,610 --> 00:22:33,330
This person, seriously...

234
00:23:32,290 --> 00:23:34,640
Whose house is this?

235
00:23:37,220 --> 00:23:40,220
Are we allowed to go in whenever?

236
00:23:42,360 --> 00:23:45,320
It's a house of someone  I know.

237
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:48,220
Come in.

238
00:23:53,170 --> 00:23:56,280
Just sit here, I'll make you some tea.

239
00:24:03,090 --> 00:24:07,940
If you're that scared of me, then tell someone that you know that we're here.

240
00:24:07,940 --> 00:24:10,370
I don't care.

241
00:24:12,210 --> 00:24:15,960
Who said I was scared?

242
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:18,400
Who is it that you know so well?

243
00:24:19,260 --> 00:24:21,060
What, I can't hear you?

244
00:24:21,060 --> 00:24:24,140
Whose house is this?

245
00:24:34,730 --> 00:24:36,240
My dad's.

246
00:24:36,240 --> 00:24:36,990
What?

247
00:24:36,990 --> 00:24:39,840
Don't touch it.

248
00:24:42,810 --> 00:24:45,230
Is this your picture?

249
00:24:45,230 --> 00:24:47,740
Yeah.

250
00:24:47,740 --> 00:24:50,600
Which one? The one on the left?

251
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:52,350
The one on the right.

252
00:24:53,900 --> 00:24:55,940
Who's the other one?

253
00:24:55,940 --> 00:24:57,630
My little brother.

254
00:24:57,630 --> 00:25:01,750
You have a brother? What does he do?

255
00:25:01,750 --> 00:25:04,160
A pianist.

256
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:08,150
Really? Is he active now?

257
00:25:11,530 --> 00:25:16,770
No, he died a year ago.

258
00:25:18,270 --> 00:25:20,400
He was murdered.

259
00:26:12,130 --> 00:26:14,370
Won't you stop filming me?

260
00:26:14,370 --> 00:26:17,800
When you film me, sunbae, I don't do so well.

261
00:26:29,850 --> 00:26:33,960
Let's go on the cable car tomorrow morning.

262
00:26:55,610 --> 00:26:59,040
I wonder if love is really a pure emotion.

263
00:27:00,010 --> 00:27:03,900
I wonder when will the moment come for love's passion to cool down.

264
00:27:05,890 --> 00:27:08,390
No one knows.

265
00:27:09,780 --> 00:27:14,620
I only know one thing,

266
00:27:29,120 --> 00:27:31,830
My frozen memories

267
00:27:32,650 --> 00:27:34,310
are beginning to move.

268
00:27:34,310 --> 00:27:36,120
Ian Kim

269
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:37,780
Mr. Ian Kim?

270
00:27:37,780 --> 00:27:39,540
No I'm not him.

271
00:27:39,540 --> 00:27:41,740
Mr. Ian Kim!

272
00:27:41,740 --> 00:27:44,330
Mr. Ian Kim?

273
00:27:44,330 --> 00:27:46,440
Excuse me!

274
00:27:51,090 --> 00:27:53,440
Kim Ian...

275
00:27:54,220 --> 00:27:56,670
Mr. Kim Ian...

276
00:28:02,620 --> 00:28:05,570
I have a lot of luggage.

277
00:28:06,700 --> 00:28:10,310
Yes? Are you talking to me?

278
00:28:10,310 --> 00:28:13,740
I have a lot of luggage, can you handle everything?

279
00:28:13,740 --> 00:28:16,150
I'm not going to help.

280
00:28:20,530 --> 00:28:22,810
Mr. Kim Ian?

281
00:28:34,890 --> 00:28:40,560
Who killed your brother?

282
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:42,780
Someone he loved.

283
00:28:47,980 --> 00:28:49,610
May I...

284
00:28:51,060 --> 00:28:54,730
ask for your brother's name?

285
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:02,900
Ian.

286
00:29:02,900 --> 00:29:07,300
Kim Ian.

287
00:29:17,970 --> 00:29:25,140
Timing and Subtitles by the Sing To Me Team @ viki

288
00:29:25,140 --> 00:29:31,630
♫ Even if it's the last time I hear your dazzling voice, it's all right ♫

289
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:40,460
♫ Please let me hear your song so that I can live ♫

290
00:29:40,460 --> 00:29:43,310
I Wanna Hear Your Song
♫ I've treasured it for a long time ♫

291
00:29:43,310 --> 00:29:46,530
You don't remember who Ian is or that he died.

292
00:29:46,530 --> 00:29:48,440
We've met before, right?

293
00:29:48,440 --> 00:29:49,890
Before we were both members of the orchestra.

294
00:29:49,890 --> 00:29:51,160
What do you like?

295
00:29:51,160 --> 00:29:52,820
I'm here to give you a welcome dinner.

296
00:29:52,820 --> 00:29:57,230
She asks me to help her sleep. We help each other sleep.

297
00:29:57,230 --> 00:29:58,750
Why are you like this to me?

298
00:29:58,750 --> 00:29:59,930
I'm no joke either.

299
00:29:59,930 --> 00:30:03,100
I am interested in Hong Yi Yeong and my heart wants to know her.

300
00:30:03,100 --> 00:30:03,970
Be careful.

301
00:30:03,970 --> 00:30:05,260
I think you're in a "some" relationship.

302
00:30:05,260 --> 00:30:08,630
Can I kiss you?

303
00:30:13,220 --> 00:30:16,150
♫ Even if I’m a flower without a scent ♫
